Fix Cflags normalization

GitHub: fix GH-25

`["-I", "/usr/include"]` should be `["-I/usr/include"]`.

Reported by Jean byroot Boussier. Thanks!!!

Add support for "<" and ">" operator in "Requires:" (#23)

https://people.freedesktop.org/~dbn/pkg-config-guide.html#concepts

> Requires: A list of packages required by this package. The versions of
these packages may be specified using the comparison operators =, <, >,
<= or >=.

commit.message: Fix a bug that success detection
Show found version on failure too

Accept spaces between '=' and ':'

For example, "prefix = /usr".

Don't use parent directory of pkg-config for default path

If "pkg-config --variable=pc_path pkg-config" works.

GitHub: fix GH-22

Reported by Watson. Thanks!!!

Use "pkg-config --variable=pc_path pkg-config" as default paths

GitHub: fix GH-22

Reported by Watson. Thanks!!!

Fix a bug that have_package can't detect nonexistent package

This is a regression in 1.4.8.
